	   <tr><td colspan=2>Being a cleric although only lvl 23, I have found that two clerics in one group can kick butt if the two clerics are both good clerics and can both work together. My normal strategy is the cleric with the better healing ability is main healer (that being the higher lvl cleric) and the other is back up. I like to get into chat with the other cleric and we both agree he let me know when he is lom or oom then i can step in with fm.&nbsp;&nbsp;Also being a back up healer i can assist the healer if he is in melie or if he needs healing.  Not to mention when you get a nice big pull and you have two characters seemingly in a race to see who can die first...But anyway i have found that if the clerics in the group remember what their primary objective is in that group one can heal and the other can, as long as they are fm, work on their hacking skills. Practice never hurts.<br><br>Sunari<br>Cleric lvl 23<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
